CCMDs with status of space forces near real time.
- Developing applications and analysis to meet space mission requirements (e.g., conjunction assessment, satellite maneuver
pattern of life, automated tools).
- Conducting orbital warfare study to inform SPAFORGEN readiness activities.
- Implementing SPAFORGEN assessment framework across 22 tactical units collecting, distilling, and analyzing after action
reports and mission reports from committed ops crews. Analysis will inform sustainment and programming efforts across the
mission areas. FY25 Expanded data sources and scope/objectives—specifically incorporating impacts of space base deltas.
- Supporting SpRCO's Remote Modular Terminal emplacement decision with operational effectiveness analysis.
- Continuing development and enhancement of SpOC/CC's ops & intel/orders management tool.
- Completing validation and verification of an advanced automated sensor calibration system for the 18 Space Defense Squadron
- Validating the S4S Laser Clearinghouse deconfliction software update.
- Delivering a satellite maneuver generation tool for tactical units training and planning development.
- Completing logistics sustainment analysis on Upgraded Early Warning Radar system.
