Title: Unified Data Library (UDL)                                                                                                         59.025          35.075      42.945
Description: UDL capabilities support integration, exploitation, and delivery of data sources for command and control and battle
management of space forces. UDL will continue to develop the library by on-boarding new data sets, directly connecting to
SDA sensors, expanding data services, expanding defensive cyber operations capabilities, adding non-metric data to the SDA
marketplace, continuing to expand local area network capability to share Space Surveillance Network (SSN) data in a cyber-
secure manner, allowing optimized data flow for use of existing SDA capability, and providing access to new commercial SDA
innovations that will enable the broader SDA mission. The UDL enables analysis across the global space enterprise, as well as for
Space Force related exercise support, cross-domain solution services and integration of the legacy communications architecture
with the UDL.

FY 2025 Plans:
Continue to expand UDL infrastructure to maintain digital superiority, supporting an increased number of providers and
consumers, and strengthening operations across multiple security environments. Continue to incorporate non-traditional and
commercial SDA data and information to improve the overall battle-space awareness for Guardians. Renew UDL's Authority to
Operate (ATO). Implement controls to monitor data egress and ingress that will result in overall reduction of cloud hosting costs.



