D. Acquisition Strategy
OCX Block 3F is a separate Acquisition Category (ACAT) II program tailored to enhance and integrate with the OCX baseline. It is part of the overall GPS Enterprise
Modernization effort. The OCX 3F development contract was awarded sole source to Raytheon Intelligence and Space on 29 Apr 21. The OCX 3F program uses an
agile software development approach to upgrade the OCX system to support the first GPS IIIF satellite launch, while also maintaining backwards compatibility for C2 of
the existing GPS satellite constellation. The program formally entered the Over-Target Baseline / Over-Target Schedule (OTB/OTS) re-baselining process on 30 May
24. The program submitted a Program Deviation Report (PDR) to the Milestone Decision Authority, the Program Executive Officer (PEO), on 9 Jul 24 concerning the
deviation to the program's final APB schedule milestone, System Integration Test (SIT). Updated APB cost and schedule milestones will be finalized in 3QFY25.



