Title: Materials/Processes for Affordable Survivability                                                                                     11.885      11.982         12.031
Description: This effort develops and matures emerging capabilities, information, and materials/processes to deliver cost-
effective technologies to enhance mission capability, ensure material integrity and mission readiness throughout the life cycle of
advanced aircraft and weapons systems for the Department of the Air Force.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue to identify and communicate best practices for ensuring repeatable quality and performance of specialty materials (e.g.,
ceramics, coatings, adhesives, resins) for assured material integrity and mission readiness throughout the life cycle of Department
of the Air Force aircraft and weapon systems. Furthermore, demonstrations will refine the understanding of material durability and
repair limits for emerging systems to reduce maintenance needs.
- Continue the acceleration of the development of advanced materials, processes, and designs to improve the durability,
maintainability, and repair of outer mold line coatings, flexible access panel treatments, and multifunctional sensor systems,
thereby increasing mission availability and readiness.
- Continue the advancement of specialty material surface treatment technologies and processes that enhance mission capability
and reduce maintenance costs.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Continue to identify and communicate best practices for ensuring repeatable quality and performance of specialty materials (e.g.,
ceramics, coatings, adhesives, resins) for assured material integrity and mission readiness throughout the life cycle of Department
of the Air Force aircraft and weapon systems. Furthermore, demonstrations will refine the understanding of material durability and
repair limits for emerging systems to reduce maintenance needs. Activities include:
-- Material selection and qualification for multiple emerging systems.
- Continue analysis of alternatives for advanced materials, processes, and designs to improve the durability, maintainability,
and repair of outer mold line coatings, flexible access panel treatments, and multifunctional sensor systems, thereby increasing
mission availability and readiness. Activities include:
-- Down-selection to most promising candidates for further advancement.
- Continue the advancement of specialty material surface treatment technologies and processes that enhance mission capability
and reduce maintenance costs. Activities include:

                                                                                                                                   Sustainment

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2025      FY 2026         FY 2027
-- Development of promising new technology capability options while working directly with multiple program offices and the
industrial base.
- Commence exploratory research, modeling, and development of polymers, responsive materials, devices, and processes to
enable increased survivability and decreased cost, size, weight and power (C-SWaP) in challenging Department of the Air Force
environments for multidomain platforms. Activities include:
-- Fabrication and assessment of novel polymer composites and devices for mission survivability and resilience.
