and DoW priorities. These efforts will address critical capability areas including, but not limited to, Autonomy Capabilities, Counter-
Air, Persistent ISR, Strategic Airlift, and Rapid Strike, all informed by Mission Engineering Threads. This work will build the
necessary evidence to support AoA Sufficiency studies at all security levels and relevant domains, delivering fully informed data
to drive acquisition decisions, inform continued development planning, and prepare for MAJCOM interactions and PPBE activities
required for PoR establishment. These products will support the Capability Development Enterprise with system attribute trades
and open system solutions, leveraging modern digital engineering tools. Where necessary, activities will involve targeted S&T
investments, risk reduction, and demonstrations to resolve technical debt, along with supporting directed studies in collaboration
with the Air Force Futures and MAJCOM.
