nuclear stockpile certification management for all AF nuclear weapon systems, and nuclear enterprise architecture alignment.

The Air Force Safety Center (AFSEC), Kirtland AFB, NM, is the primary executing agency for nuclear weapons certification. The AFSEC is tasked with providing safety,
control, and operational policy and independent assessments and expertise used for the US nuclear enterprise, US nuclear weapons and nuclear weapon system
programs as well as security of nuclear weapon design information. This program provides resources for oversight, technical and programmatic activities which include
research, development, test, and evaluation of all nuclear weapon related equipment/systems, as well as performing independent analyses on all AF nuclear weapon
