-The first operational release of CTEN is scheduled for early 2026 followed by another release later in 2026. Both will be
integrated on Phalanx Nomad hardware baseline with final delivery of full Phalanx Griffon (PG)-system to F15 SPO in calendar
year 2026. This includes software Model Based System Engineering artifacts
-Complete systems architecting and continue to support advanced non-proprietary antenna apertures necessary to mature the
Enterprise Approach to the Joint Aerial Network.
-Complete systems architecture with associated CTEN reference architecture Model Based System Engineering artifacts.
-Develop software sustainment plan and contract award.
FY 2027 Plans:
-Will continue to execute software releases, integration, and demonstrations.
-Will continue to engineer the capability to provide data routing critical to the operation of PG/C3HST and the associated Phalanx
Watch network support function.
-Will continue to upgrade software as the ability to scale CTEN and integrate increased ground nodes and weapons platforms will
continue as PG expands.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Decrease from FY 2026 to FY 2027 due to realignment for higher operational priorities.
Title: MBeam                                                                                                                              0.000        0.000        50.796
Description: Funds will develop advanced data links to support current and future warfighter needs in evolving threat landscapes.
MBeam is a protected, scalable, and open-designed waveform that is directional, anti-jam, supports large, dense, mesh networks
operating using internet protocol (IP), permits ad-hoc networks, and government-owned.

FY 2026 Plans:
