Description: These funds address the enduring requirement for long range surveillance beyond line of sight data link where
satellite communications or alternate connectivity is not available. Link 11 is currently the only data link capable but is now past
its sundown date. Funds will provide for research, development, testing and evaluation of Link 22 systems to replace the Link 11
systems in NORAD, Control and Reporting Centers (CRCs), Battle Control Centers (BCCs) and Air Operations Centers (AOCs)
across the Air Force.

